==English==

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæk.tʃu.ə.li/
*{{audio|en-us-actually.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adverb===
#In act or [[in fact]]; [[really]]; [[in truth]]; [[positively]]

===Usage note===
In some [[Romance]] languages a word of similar spelling means "now" or "currently"; e.g., Spanish "[[actualmente]]". This leads many non-native speakers of English to use "actually" when they mean "now".

===Synonyms===
*[[in reality]]
*[[literally]]
*[[really]]
*[[truthfully]]

